Part 1: Get the Windows 11 ISO
  1. Go to the Microsoft Evaluation Center 
  2. Downlaod the Winodws 11 Enterprise ISO


Part 2: Create the Virtual Machine in VMWare
  1. In VMWare Workstation Pro click File > New Virtual Machine
  2. Select Typical > Select Installer disc image file (ISO) - I don't have much experience with VMWare and wanted to try the simplier/auto install as opposed to the more custom install I did with the server.
  3. Virtual Machine Name: Win11-Client-01
  4. Select "Only the files needed to support a TPM are encrypted". > Password: Password123
  5. Maximum disk size: 64 GB (You need to be careful here, Windows 11 requires 64 GB so you need to keep this at a minumum)
  6. Leave Memory: 4 GB, CPUS core: 2
  7. Click Finish

Part 3 - Install Winodws 11
  1. When the VM starts, click inside the black screen and press a key on your keyboard when it says "Press any key to book from CD or DVD.."
  2. Windows Setup flow: English > Custom: Install Winodws only > Click through until you get to account sign-in
  3. Select Sign-in options > Domain join instead
  4. Who's going to use this device: LocalAdmin, Password: Password123
  5. Complete privacy questions and finish
